children.subject: I think it'll still count as a CS upper div tech in the future fwiw
Yeah it's the same class, just offered by the division of data science now
I was concerned about that too! I saw that CS C100 is closed but Data C100 is open. Can CS majors enroll in Data C100 and it still counts as a non-elective upper div?

history.content:
I am planning on taking DATA100 next spring, but looking at the class on the academic guide it looks like the class will no longer be listed as COMPSCI/STAT C100, presumably due to the data science major being approved.

I've read policies regarding cross-listed classes, and I know taking it before as STAT C100 wouldn't count towards the non-cs tech requirement due to it being cross-listed as COMPSCI C100.  But now that the class is under DATA and is no longer cross-listed, is it reasonable to assume that DATA100 could count as an approved Non-CS Technical elective in the future?
history.subject: DATA100 as a Non-CS Technical Elective?
